{
  "stem": "26142.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "We coped-- The-- the Jews were not allowed to be in-- in-- in the lumber business.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "But we-- we tried to-- to-- to find loopholes in the law.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And one of the loopholes was that if you found what we call at that time [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH] is literally a front, a person.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "It-- it was a-- it had to be a Gentile that took over-- performed the business, became the be official owner, and the real owners were getting some-- some part of it.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And that went on-- that went on for-- for another-- another year or so.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "Since we did business, my father did business under the Czechs yet with a-- a firm from Budapest, and that-- one of their representatives, their firm's, the firm's name was [?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "Halos. ?] They were-- they were-- that was a Jewish firm in Budapest, but they employed a German by the name of Schrammel.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And, you know, this business was you bought something that will be delivered in a half a year, three quarters of a year.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "So they-- the way the work progressed, their representative would tell them that so-- so much work is done, and that's how they would pay.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "They wouldn't pay at-- at-- up front.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "They would pay up front a certain amount but not-- not what it costs to-- to-- to cut it and to bring it out.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this guy, Schrammel, my father knew him and had connections with him, so he became, all of a sudden, he became the owner.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he-- he was the [NON-ENGLISH], and we were able to more or less breathe.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was in '39.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In '40, it started getting worse.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
